messages.text: You have to get me out of here.
This cat is going to kill me.
The cat’s not going to kill you mom.
It just killed Mrs. Henderson yesterday. She was only two rooms from me!
Mrs. Henderson passed? That’s too bad, she was such a nice lady.
The cat was in the room. I saw him cut her oxygen tube.
He was probably just comforting her. You know how they say animals can sense when you are sick or dying.
I saw him perched over her!
Did you remember to take your pills mom? You know how antsy you get and start seeing things.
David I know what I saw. Ever since you brought the cat here it’s been killing off the residents one by one.
I think you’ve been watching too much TV mom.
Why don’t believe me?
Because the cat is not going to kill you. It’s a cat.
You should have just gotten me a dog. Dogs don’t try to kill their owners and their friends.
Just yesterday he darted under my feet and tried to trip me when I was doing my rehab.
He probably just wanted to say hi.
That cat is evil.
It scratched the hell out of poor Mr. Edelman and gave him the infection that killed him.
It snuck into Mrs. Tibalt’s room and made her go into anaphylactic shock.
Everywhere that cat has gone it’s brought death.
The staff says you haven’t been eating well.
It’s because I can’t leave my room. It’s the only safe place for me.
I think if you ate something and left your room you’d feel better.
David, that cat owns this building. It could be lurking anywhere, waiting for me to make a mistake.
I want to get out of here. I don’t like it. I don’t feel safe.
Do you want me to call one of the assistants? Maybe they can calm you down.
I don’t want them to come in, the cat might follow. Can’t you come and get me out of this place?
I can’t mom, you know that. I’m three time zones away.
But can’t you just move me somewhere else?
Do you want me to FaceTime with you? Would that help?
For what? So you can watch me get killed?
Mom.
No, no I understand. Why bother to visit your own mother? You have your life with Audrey and the kids.
Why bother talking to your lunatic mom as she tries to avoid being killed by Kevorkian Kitty.
The cat’s not going to kill you. I bought it so you could have a companion.
Well great job. It’s really kind of you David. It’s only been systematically killing off all my neighbors one by one.
And now it is focusing its claws on me.
Where did you find it, wandering the gates of hell or perhaps running through the neighborhood with old people’s dead dangling off its tail?
Do you think this will get you your inheritance faster? Is that you’re plan?
I’m not going to be another victim!
You’re becoming hysterical, Mom. You need to calm down or I will have to call Dr. Jones in.
Don’t you dare have that doctor come in here.
You need to take your pills or they’ll have to come in and sedate you.
Please don’t. I need to be alert. I can’t let my guard down.
Just take one of your pills. It will relax you.
Ok.
Why don’t you put on a movie or read one of your magazines?
Yes… Yes. Maybe I should do that.
I think I am feeling a little better.
That’s good Mom.
David, I’m not crazy. I’m really not.
You believe me right?
I know Mom.
The cat really is evil.
Okay Mom.
I just want to get out of here. Can’t you get me out of here?
I will Mom.
You will?
I will.
I’m sorry. I’m sorry that I’m like this. I’ve been in this room for so long and that cat is everywhere.
I know it’s trying to get me.
It’s okay Mom.
I’m just going to close my eyes for a little bit.
That’s a good idea.
I had the worst dream. I dreamt that the cat had snuck into the room.
He whispered how he was going to end my life.
Probably just the pills Mom.
It felt so real. He told me to wake up and watch.
Oh my God, David. David, the cat’s in the room.
What?
He’s in here! I don’t know how but he’s here.
Go back to sleep mom, you’re still hallucinating.
No he’s in the corner. I can see his eyes. They’re the eyes of the devil.
It’s okay.
Oh God he’s going to kill me.
He’s on the bed. I can’t move. I can’t move!
It’s alright mom he’s here to help.
He’s on my chest.
Just give him a scratch.
His tails around my neck.
Everything will be alright.
I don’t want to die.
Close your eyes mom. It will all be over soon.
